acts interpretation act 1901 (cth.), s. 15a. the applicant was a professional footballer with the west perth club. he sought a clearance to play for the norwood football club in adelaide. the two clubs were both members of their respective state football leagues. both state leagues were members of the national football league. the heirarchy of leagues and clubs, of which the respondents were part, imposed on players the rules of the national football league. those rules included the clearance and permit regulations which imposed restrictions on the ability of players to change clubs.
